            <p>
               <persName ref="pers:HOLT1">Hon. Mr. Holton</persName> said he was actuated by no 
     <lb/>
     hostility towards the gentleman who occupied 
     <lb/>
     the office- far from it- but he had taken the 
     <lb/>
     ground all through the discussion on the sub<lb break="no"/>ject that they had too many offices. 
     <lb/>
            </p>
   
            <p>
     It now being six o'clock, the house rose. 
     <lb/>
            </p>
   
            <p>
     <emph>After recess,</emph> 
     <lb/>
            </p>
   
            <p>
     <persName ref="pers:MACD1">Hon. Sir John A. Macdonald</persName> said that as 
     <lb/>
    Hon. Mr. Howe was not present, he would 
     <lb/>
     move the adjournment of the debate on the Bill 
     <lb/>
     relating to the organization of the Department 
     <lb/>
     of Secretary of State- Carried. 
     <lb/>
            </p>
           
            
            
